Description: Rest on flight into Egypt, with Virgin holding Christ Child in her arms and sitting on the parapet of a fountain; St Joseph leans on the other side of the fountain and points at a broken statue lying on the ground, on the left counterproof of early state, before letter and before additional work on Virgin's face Etching
Curator's comments: From a series of six, see 1856,0815.26.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: William Fawkener (WF initials on recto in ink)
